This weekend we had some fun making food! I cooked escargot au gratin (just like in Quebec!) and my favorite Russian dessert, муравейник (muraveinik means ant hill, as little poppy seeds on top look like ants🤣).

 Had an amazing Napa wine from V Sattui (love this winery!) with the escargot. 

Huge thanks to our dear friend Joelle for the tips and advice on escargot-making❤️

P.S. In the pic you see us getting the dough through the meatgrinder (which I got in Moscow JUST for this dessert🤣!) to give it better texture and shape. Baby V loved that!

Yesterday afternoon I shot liquid soap right into my eye. 
Accidentally, obviously :)
It was in a public bathroom and Violetta was next to me. 
It burned like hell. I think I screamed and scared V :)
Then spent a lot of time flushing it out. 

It also happened to be my one good eye. Yup. The other eye has been not so good since childhood.
This laughing/crying emoji is a perfect illustration of yesterday😂

Today the eye is better but not yet 100%.
I'm moving tonight's stream to tomorrow (Weds, 6pm PST).

Does anyone have "soap meets eye" stories to share? :)

Today I'm sending a video of my first ever public performance to our 2 Songs a Month Club on patreon.com/MarinaV !! I was a student at Illinois College & sang my song "Leaving" at the school talent show. I was so nervous I was shaking, but somehow they gave me the first prize. 

That night was pivotal in my music life as it set me on a career path as a performing singer/songwriter. I hadn't seen this footage in years, but on the day of my 1,500th concert last week Nick's best friend Steve (who filmed this performance) suggested I share it on Twitch. So I found the footage and shared a short clip. Here's an even shorter clip, haha. 🙂 

Please join my 2 Songs a Month Club if you'd like to see the whole 4.5 min video.

I am now a rapper 🤣  For the last 2 years I've been adapting songs from Russian into English for 3 popular children's YouTube channels including Meow Meow Kitty, which now has over 1.5 million subscribers!

 I write the English lyrics, then record a demo for the 5 singers/voice actors (which I had found and auditioned. Extra shout out to @crossovercrrissa and @jasenrcolson , my first "finds"🙂❤️). 

It all started when Baby V fell in love with Blue Tractor on YouTube. And now, to my utter surprise, working on kids songs has become a huge part of my life. And sometimes I even get to rap🤣

It brings me so much joy,  and it is fun as hell! Спасибо тебе, @dneprovsky !

Before we had  our beautiful Baby V I really had no clue why couples had " date nights". But, as a mom of an almost 4 year old,  now I know well how very important it is to attempt to maintain your identity as a person, and together as a couple, and not only exist as a parent. Easier said than done, as Nick & I both work from home. Also, babysiters ain't free🤣 

How do you find your balance? I feel it is an ongoing process for me...

[Pics from the wonderful Tierra Sur last week, Nick & I had a really nice time, and I asked him to take a video of me in my new skirt, exciting🙂]

Not sure if you knew, but Nick has been a teacher at @cavak12 for over 2 decades now, and received his doctorate in education from Northeastern University in Boston a couple years ago.

He's dedicated himself to turning his dissertation into this book, and then tirelessly worked with the team at Rowman & Littlefield to publish it.

Please join me in wishing the happiest of birthdays to Nick (a.k.a. dr Daddy) today!!!

 He is truly the love of my life. A girl from Moscow, Russia, and a boy from Springfield, IL, happen to meet one night in a jacuzzi at a fitness club. Pretty crazy how fate brought us together.

We've been life partners for a quarter century now. We've written hundreds of songs, spent tens of thousands of hours touring together, have seen a lot of this beautiful world, and supported each other through everything. And now we have a cute little treasure named Violetta. 

Nick is easy going but tough. Relaxed yet very focused (he finished his PhD and released a book!)
He brings out the best in every person he meets.
He definitely brings out the best in me.

Happy birthday, my smart beautiful husband / best daddy to our little girl!!

Did you know that my online concerts (Twitch streams) are not just about music? ❤ It is as much about everyone in the chat - our community - as it is about me singing songs. 

We have a caring group of people with several regulars and plenty of new people each time. 

We share, tell jokes, empathize, get silly and get serious, and occasionally even cry. Sometimes, it's even a group therapy session of sorts 🙂 

But you don't have to chat if you don't want to. You can just watch or be as active and anonymous/open as you want to be. 

You request songs, I sing, and we chat in between. 

If you're new, we will welcome you with open arms. 

If you're returning to Marinawood, we welcome you back with zombie hugs (an inside joke you'll learn if you tune in) 🙂 

It is free & fun! 

and yes, Marinawood! :) That's what we call our community, thanks to Steve, our mod, for this name:) 

The next stream is this Friday, Nov 17th at 12:30pm PT.

Happy anniversary, my love! Nick & I have been together for over 20 years, have written hundreds of songs, performed 1,200+ concerts, and traveled a LOT. 

My point is that we are a couple that has spent most of their time together, not apart. 

We have driven at least 500k miles (800,000 km) over the years (according to odometers), and people often asked, especially at shows, "How do you do it? To be together ALL the time, in a car and working together? Don't you get on each other's nerves? " 

Once in a great while, yes🤣 But somehow spending the majority of our time together has always felt right. 

Every day, I realize how lucky we are to have found each other. And now, with our amazing little daughter, our relationship feels even better.

 Are we perfect? Yes, yes, we are! 🤣 But seriously, of course not. However, time and time again, through the very hardest moments to the happiest, we know we are meant to be. This is our own little Modern Fairytale 😊❤️🎶 

P.S. Photo from a few days ago at Taix in Los Angeles. It's one of our faves, and it's been operating since 1927!
